{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, this model is quite general and subsumes various choice models typically considered in assortment optimization such as the MNL (see Mahajan and van Ryzin 2001).",
    "As mentioned before, the parameters of the parametric choice models introduced so far are typically unknown and therefore need to be chosen.",
    "The same holds for the descriptors of nonparametric models such as the empirical distribution of a demand function.",
    "For this purpose, data are required, whereby the data used for such estimation tasks can consist of stated-preference or revealed-preference data.",
    "Stated-preference data comprise data that are based on behavioural intentions and responses to hypothetical choice situations, whereas revealed-preference data describe actual customer behaviour (see Ben-Akiva 1994)."
  ]
}